      <section eId="sec_13_3_46">
        <num>13-3-46</num>
        <content>
          <p>Mere inadequacy of consideration alone will not void a contract. If the inadequacy is great, it is a strong circumstance to evidence fraud; and, in an action for damages for breach of a contract, the inadequacy of consideration will always enter as an element in estimating the damages.</p>
          <p>(Orig. Code 1863, § 2706; Code 1868, § 2700; Code 1873, § 2742; Code 1882, § 2742; Civil Code 1895, § 3659; Civil Code 1910, § 4244; Code 1933, § 20-307.)</p>
        </content>
